PSUDO CODE


Passwords Must be at least 8 characters long.
contain at least:
one alpha character [a-zA-Z];
one numeric character [0-9];
one character that is not alpha or numeric (! # @ $ % for example but this is just a subset, 
it could be any character that you can type that is not a letter or number) 
Passwords Must Not

contain spaces;
begin with an exclamation [!] or a question mark [?];
contain repeating character strings of 3 or more identical characters, such as "1111" or "aaa".
Your task is to create a project to verify whether or not a prospective proper password meets these 
requirements and that the user has entered the correct password twice.

The project should identify to the user the types of rule violations that are contained in an improperly 
entered password.